   Communicating with the Federal Reserve Board

      Because paper mail in the Washington area and at the Board of Governors
      is subject to delay, please consider using these options when
      communicating with us:

      Comments on regulations can be submitted by e-mail to
      regs.comments@federalreserve.gov, submitted electronically, or faxed to
      the Office of the Secretary at 202-452-3819 or 202-452-3102.

      Comments on banking applications can be faxed to the Office of the
      Secretary at 202-452-3819 or 202-452-3102.

      Requests for information can be submitted electronically or faxed to
      the Freedom of Information Office at 202-872-7565.

      Requests for publications can be faxed to the Publications Services
      Unit at 202-728-5886 or made by phone at 202-452-3245. A publications
      order form can be found at www.federalreserve.gov/pubs/order.htm.
      Subscription payments can be made by credit card.

      General correspondence can be faxed to 202-452-3819 or submitted on our
      temporary e-mail form.
